# Backend Standards — Suryamas ERP

Single source of truth for new backend code. All new modules **must** follow this.

## Module structure (mandatory)

Every module under `backend/src/modules/*`:

- `*.routes.ts`, `*.controller.ts`, `*.service.ts`, `*.repository.ts`, `*.schema.ts`, `*.errors.ts`, `*.types.ts`
- All layers required — no skipping
- No cross-layer access (controller → repository ❌)

## Middleware order (fixed)

```
authenticate → resolveBranchContext → requireWriteAccess (mutations) → permission → validateSchema
```

Use: `auth.middleware`, `branch-context.middleware`, `permission.middleware`, `validation.middleware`. Permissions: `canView`, `canInsert`, `canUpdate`, `canDelete`, `canApprove`, `canRelease`. Schema validation **only** in routes.

```typescript
router.get(
  '/',
  canView(MODULE),
  validateSchema(schema),
  (req, res) => controller.method(req, res)
)
```

Static routes (`/search`, `/bulk/delete`, `/trash`) **before** `/:id`.

## Layer contracts

| Layer | Do | Don't |
|-------|-----|-------|
| **Controller** | `withValidated`, `sendSuccess`, `await handleError(res, error, req, context)` | Business logic, DB queries |
| **Service** | Business logic, transactions, `AuditService.log` on CREATE/UPDATE/DELETE/RESTORE | Direct DB access |
| **Repository** | DB only; filter `company_id` + `deleted_at IS NULL`; JOIN/batch, no N+1 | Business logic |
| **Schema** | `import { z } from '@/lib/openapi'`; `.coerce` (query), `.refine` (business) | Raw `zod` import |

## Errors

- Custom errors from `*.errors.ts` — never `throw new Error()`
- Register new classes in `src/config/error-registry.ts`
- `await handleError(res, error, req, context)` with metadata `{ action, id?, query }`
- `isPostgresError(err, '23505')` from `src/utils/postgres-error.util.ts`

## Context & types

- `company_id` from `req.context?.company_id` — **not** query param
- Audit (`created_by`, `updated_by`, `posted_by`, journal `*_by`): **`req.user.id`** (`auth_users`) — helper `getAuthUserId(req)`
- `req.context?.employee_id` hanya untuk konteks cabang/HR (`employees`), **bukan** kolom audit
- Express augmentation in `src/types/express.d.ts` — **no** `req as any`
- DTOs include `created_by` / `updated_by`
- After `.ts` changes: `cd backend && npx tsc`

## Audit log (mutations)

`user_id`, `action`, `entity`, `entity_id`, `before`, `after`, `timestamp` via `AuditService.log`.

## Search + pagination (mandatory)

Filter in SQL first, then `LIMIT/OFFSET`. `COUNT(*)` uses the same `WHERE`. Frontend resets to page 1 on search/filter change. Use `search` key (not `q`) for text filters unless reading `req.query.q` manually.

## Performance & security

- No N+1; pagination on all list APIs
- All endpoints: authenticated, authorized, validated
- S3/R2: lazy getter (`getS3()`), `forcePathStyle: true`
- Dates: backend ISO / `YYYY-MM-DD`; frontend display `dd-MMM-yyyy`
